HEADWORD: Whitsuntide
<hw>Whit"sun*tide`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Whitsunday</ets> + <ets>tide</ets>.]</ety> <def>The week
commencing with Whitsunday, esp. the first three days -- Whitsunday,
Whitsun Monday, and Whitsun Tuesday; the time of Pentecost.</def>
<rj><au>R. of Gloucester.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

